{"key":"post-9344897","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9344897</id>\n<content>I'd find a blower that can deliver 500 to 600 cfm at 1&quot; static pressure for a 2 X 2 blower.&amp;nbsp; You want about 400 to 450 cfm leaving the face of the filter, but since blowers are not 100% efficient, and the fact that you'll have friction, etc., you want to add 20% or so.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You should be able to go to a local furnace repair shop and they probably have a few junked out old units in the back that they'll sell a blower cheaply from.&amp;nbsp; Let them know what cfm you're looking for and they can try to match it.&amp;nbsp; If the motor is slightly too large, you can always block off part of the intake to cut down on flow, or purchase a &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.littlegreenhouse.com/accessory/controls2.shtml&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;motor speed controller&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>9343020</prev>\n<first>9323247</first>\n<last>9344897</last>\n<when>1228170212</when>\n<utime>12/02/08 12:23 AM</utime>\n</post>"}